cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.HC 

The paper proposes a deep learning computer vision framework for measuring human activities in public open spaces. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The study also involves behavioral mapping, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of physical activities and social interactions, which could be related to cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
